gantt
Section Prepare Marinade
Peel and smash 5 cloves of garlic and add to a mixing bowl :a, 2010-01-01, 3d
Add 2 cups buttermilk, 1 TBSP table salt, 1 TBSP granulated sugar, 1.5 TSP paprika and 2 TSP freshly ground black pepper and whisk together :b, after a, 5d
Place 3lbs chicken thighs in gallon-sized freezer bag and pour buttermilk brine over them, swish it around so that all parts are covered and refrigerate overnight :c, after b, 1440d
Section Roast Chicken 
Preheat oven to 425 degrees :d, after c, 20d
Line a baking tray with foil :e, after c, 1d
Remove chicken from buttermilk brine and arrange on baking tray :f, after e, 2d
Drizzle lightly with olive oil, then sprinkle with additional paprika and flaky sea salt to taste :g, after f, 2d
Roast until brown and a bit scorched in spots :crit, h, after g d, 30d
Serve immediately :I, after h, 1d
&&&
2 cups buttermilk
5 garlic cloves, peeled and smashed
1 tablespoon table salt
1 tablespoon granulated sugar
1 1/2 teaspoons paprika, plus extra for sprinkling (I used Hungarian, a smoked one would also be delicious)
Lots of freshly ground black pepper
2 1/2 to 3 pounds chicken parts (we used all legs)
Drizzle of olive oil
Flaked or coarse sea salt, to finish
